2. Statistics
According to the World Health Organization (WHO), over 1.9 billion people suffer from skin diseases globally.
More than 50% of people with skin issues do not seek medical attention due to cost, accessibility, or lack of awareness.
Studies show that AI-powered diagnostic tools have an accuracy rate of up to 90% in identifying skin conditions.
The dermatology market is expected to grow to $40 billion by 2030, highlighting the increasing demand for skin-related healthcare solutions.
